### Baguette Side Stone Settings

[![Three-Stone Tapered Baguette Diamond Engagement Ring in 14K white gold](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/BrioSuperImposeBox/Rings/501720/501720_M1_EMR_DIM_wht_0100CT_R_Box3_004_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?styleIDs=three_stone&MetalType=all&Diamonds=Dia&ShapeID=Emerald&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

Baguette side stones are the most historically grounded choice for an emerald cut three-stone ring. The step-cut geometry echoes the center, and the narrow rectangular shape adds length without height. These settings work especially well in yellow gold — the warm metal against the clean lines of the baguette sides and emerald cut center is the canonical Art Deco look.

