      <td><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/three-stone-tapered-baguette-diamond-engagement-ring-in-platinum-5-8-ct-tw-item-191941?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational">$7,630</a></td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

**Baguette clarity note:** The JA Bezel Straight Baguette settings use bezel-set baguettes — the metal wraps around the side stones. This actually helps with two things: it protects the baguette's vulnerable corners, and the bezel metal partially covers the side stone face, reducing the open-table visibility that would otherwise expose SI1 inclusions. Bezel baguettes are slightly more forgiving on side stone clarity than prong-set baguettes.

### Trapezoid Side Stone Settings

[![Bella Vaughan Trapezoid Three Stone Engagement Ring in 14K yellow gold](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/BrioSuperImposeBox/Rings/502483/502483_M1_EMR_DIM_wht_0100CT_Y_Box3_003_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?styleIDs=three_stone&MetalType=all&Diamonds=Dia&ShapeID=Emerald&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

Trapezoid side stones are the modern refinement of the baguette approach. They taper inward toward the band, framing the center stone and drawing the eye to its center. The Bella Vaughan designs are the benchmark for this style.

