## 3 Stone Emerald Cut Lab Grown Diamond Ring

[![Three-stone emerald cut diamond engagement ring with pavé set diamonds in 14K yellow gold](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/BrioPackshotBox/Rings/502487/502487_M1_EMR_DIM_wht_0100CT_Y_Box5_003_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?styleIDs=three_stone&MetalType=all&Diamonds=Dia&ShapeID=Emerald&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

Lab grown diamonds are the obvious choice for a three-stone ring center. You are buying one stone and paying the full per-carat price for that stone. In a three-stone format, the center stone needs to be larger than the sides by the 35–40% rule. That means at minimum a 1.5ct center — ideally 2ct or more. At 2ct natural, you are spending [$24,407](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/14013191?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) before touching the setting. At 2ct lab D-FL, you are spending [$4,735](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28828463?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational).

