## 5 Stone and 7 Stone Emerald Cut Diamond Ring

The 5 stone and 7 stone emerald cut rings follow the same geometry rule as the 3 stone — additional side stones work best when they are step cuts. Adding two more step-cut side elements to the flanking position creates a wider band of horizontal step facets across the finger. The overall effect is more ornate but the architectural logic stays intact.

For a 5 stone emerald cut ring, the typical configuration is: main center stone, two flanking side stones (trapezoid or baguette), and two outer accent stones (smaller baguettes or trapezoids). The Gallery Collection Vintage Three Stone Trapezoid settings use this approach:

