## 3 Stone Emerald Cut Diamond Ring Wedding Band Compatibility

One practical question buyers miss: does the three-stone ring sit flush with a wedding band? Most three-stone rings have a wider profile at the setting than the band allows for a straight-shank band to sit flush.

Two solutions:
1. Choose a contoured/curved wedding band that is shaped to fit around the three-stone setting's profile.
2. Wear the wedding band on the other hand.

For the JA Emerald Cut Three Stone Pavé settings, the design is flat enough that a standard straight band can sit reasonably close — there will be a small gap at the setting shoulders, which is normal. The Bella Vaughan Trapezoid has a wider shoulder that creates more of a gap.

A [trapezoid sidestone setting in rose gold at $5,900](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/three-stone-trapezoid-sidestone-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-rose-gold-1-2-ct-tw-item-203681?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) or the [trapezoid in platinum at $6,890](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/three-stone-trapezoid-sidestone-diamond-engagement-ring-in-platinum-1-2-ct-tw-item-192941?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) pair well with a matching curved band in the same metal. Discuss band compatibility with the jeweler before committing to the setting.

