## Final Verdict

**Best under $10,000:** [JA Pavé Platinum ($3,700)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/emerald-cut-diamond-three-stone-engagement-ring-with-pave-set-diamonds-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-304297?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) + [2ct D-FL lab ($4,735)](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28828463?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) ≈ $8,435 total. Emerald cut side stones, platinum durability, 2ct center. The strongest overall value in this dataset.

**Best architecture:** [Bella Vaughan Trapezoid WG ($9,115)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/bella-vaughan-trapezoid-three-stone-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-5-8-ct-tw-item-203559?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) + [2ct D-FL lab ($4,735)](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28828463?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) ≈ $13,850 total. True Bella Vaughan trapezoid geometry — the most architecturally correct three-stone emerald cut design available.

**Best for yellow gold:** [Zac Zac Posen Three-Stone Emerald ($3,460)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/zac-zac-posen-three-stone-emerald-cut-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-1-3-ct-tw-item-203528?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) + [2ct D-FL lab ($4,735)](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28828463?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) ≈ $8,195 total. The delicate shank and warm yellow gold frame an emerald cut the way vintage rings do — the geometry is right and the metal choice is correct.

**Best presence:** [JA Pavé Platinum ($3,700)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/emerald-cut-diamond-three-stone-engagement-ring-with-pave-set-diamonds-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-304297?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) + [3ct D-IF lab ($9,235)](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28885081?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) ≈ $12,935 total. A 3ct D-IF center in a three-stone setting is a ring that fills a finger. The IF clarity through the open emerald cut table is exceptionally clean. For buyers who want a serious, noticeable stone, this is where to end up.

